      "end_time": 177800.0,
      "text": "Great idea."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 182800.0,
      "end_time": 189000.0,
      "text": "Two chlorine atoms come together and share their electrons to form a molecule of chlorine."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 190500.0,
      "end_time": 202000.0,
      "text": "In this way, each atom will have eight electrons in its valence shell."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 203800.0,
      "end_time": 213000.0,
      "text": "As a single pair of electrons is shared between them, the bond is known as a single covalent bond."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 215180.0,
      "end_time": 221700.0,
      "text": "A single covalent bond is represented by a single dash between the atoms."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 222300.0,
      "end_time": 223100.0,
      "text": "Great."
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 224000.0,
      "end_time": 224700.0,
